snippet.textDisplay: So in answer to the question "why aren't there restaurants that do this?" A lot of people believe the answer is the sugar industry. Miracle berries grabbed the attention a diet food manufacturer in the late 60s and early 70s as a way of making truly sugar free and sweetener free foods. This could have cut deep into the profits of the sugar industry. Right before the launch of miracle berry "sweetened" line of food products the FDA suddenly changed the berries statue from "safe" to "food additive" which meant that ton more research would have needed to be done to get it cleared. The company that was working on making it couldnt afford the reasearch so it died. A lot of people believe that the sugar industry lobbied hard and pressured the FDA to try and kill the competition and it worked.
